parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the serpentine belt can cause the loss of power steering, power brakes, and engine overheating, leading to hazardous driving conditions.
symptoms: The serpentine belt detaches from the pulleys
causing the loss of power steering
power brakes
and engine overheating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause the loss of power and control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls without warning
sometimes with a loud noise or loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cooling system failure can cause engine overheating, leading to engine damage or failure.
symptoms: The cooling system fails to function properly
causing the engine to overheat.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system failure can cause the loss of critical systems, such as power steering and power brakes, leading to hazardous driving conditions.
symptoms: The electrical system fails to function properly
causing the loss of power steering
power brakes
or other critical systems.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission failure can cause the loss of power and control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission fails to function properly
causing the loss of power or control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clock spring can cause the airbag light to illuminate, the horn to malfunction, and the cruise control to fail, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The airbag light is on
the horn does not work
the cruise control does not work
the clock spring is broken
and the vehicle's electrical system is malfunctioning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause injuries or fatalities in the event of a crash, as the airbags may not deploy or may deploy improperly.
symptoms: The airbag did not deploy
the airbag deployed late
the airbag deployed with excessive force
the passenger airbag deployed but not the driver's airbag
and the seat came off track during the crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the manufacturer to notify owners of safety recalls or to repair recalled vehicles can lead to accidents or injuries due to known safety defects.
symptoms: The owner was not notified of a safety recall
the dealership refused to repair the vehicle under recall
the recall repair was not done correctly
and the owner was denied reimbursement for recall repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. In some cases, it can also cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
the transmission fluid leaks
the vehicle makes a loud banging or grinding noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Differential pin failure can cause the transmission to fail, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission fails
the vehicle makes a loud banging or grinding noise
the transmission fluid leaks
the vehicle stalls or loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Parking gear failure can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle shifts out of park unexpectedly
the vehicle rolls or moves unexpectedly while in park.
